ReviewContent: Such a unique and beautiful place to study!
This is a peaceful place to study. It feels like a little sanctuary hidden from the bustle of SF.

How have I slept on this treasure? Amazing tea house and yoga studio, take your shoes off at the door, indulge your senses in the smells of brewing teas, chocolate, the gentle vibrations of conversations and hushed voices interspersed with laughter and the sounds of classes starting and stopping. Yoga Nidra with Miguel was great, I ll be back.

Amazing yoga studio in San Francisco! I liked that they have kundalini yoga classes a lot in a week schedule! The cafe is amazing. Very spacious, cozy atmosphere, many yoga people are chilling on the couches! Our recommended studio in San Francisco! There were many types of Kundalini yoga. The cafe attached to the studio was wonderful, and many yogis were relaxing on the sofas.
Beautiful space, I wish I came sooner. 10/10
A home away from home. Great vibes, conscious community and alcohol free!
they have sound baths and yogi stuff like that

Wonderful place, great energy, kind people, great offerings! My only reason for not giving 5 stars was being on the receiving end of a business policy with which I strongly disagree and hope will change. I was 10-15 min late to the 9am yoga class and wasnt able to get in the building. I waited outside for about 10-15 min and was about to leave when an employee walked by outside and noticed me and let me in. This was only half the battle and I also needed to get the attention of the people inside the yoga class via an open window to get in the next door. Once let in I was initially met with some friction, and was told that the doors lock 10 minutes after the start of yoga class out of respect for the teacher, and was told adamantly that thats the businesses policy. Now I certainly agree that students should make every effort to arrive on time. However, this is the real world in the SF Bay Area. People can be making a tremendous effort to get there, waking up at 7:30am, driving from 45 min away from the peninsula or Silicon Valley (as I did), people can get stuck in traffic, have trouble finding a parking spot. In my opinion turning such people away and leaving them locked outside for not arriving on time is cold and unfriendly, and not an approach that should be adopted by a healing center, whose goal is hopefully to spread love in the world. IMO doors should be open and customers/patrons should be welcomed with open arms. If certain people habitually arrive late each week, they can be talked to about it separately. I think this kind of balance and open mindedness is important in finding creative solutions to problems. Solutions that are uncreative and inflexible are usually rooted in some kind of fear, and should be what any kind of healing or spiritual center worth its salt should seek to transcend. I hope that in the future the policies of this center will be kind, accepting, and welcoming to all members, regardless of some occasionally poor punctuality ;)

a refreshingly genuine experience. High proportion of good, authentic people. There are commercial aspects, but handled properly to preserve spiritual feel. I wish there was a better way to purchase items inside without digging for your phone or wallet- perhaps we can open a  tab   at the door or setup an account in advance?
charming spot for a pot of tea. calming, tables and seating on floor, community events.

This place is well decorated with a spiritual vibe. Plus the drinks are  very good. I enjoyed the dirty/golden (sorry I forgot the exact name) latte while my friend got matcha latte. We both like our drinks. I like how the shop has the sitting places on the floor which gives a unique experience here.
Hidden gem in SF! Comfortable and calming seating along with nice cup of tea!

Love this place! Will absolutely be back :) Had an afternoon tea and read a to share astrology book they had on a shelf :) then I attended a lovely cacao ceremony later in the evening :)    the perfect spot :) planning to go back tomorrow with my journal for more tea and to hopefully pour over the astrology book again :) met some really cool people too!
Amazing place for cup of tea!

If this spot isn t representative of San Francisco, then I don t know what is. I went here with a few friends and firstly this spot is so communal. You can just sit anywhere there is space with anyone else and it s so cute and beautiful- great for making some new friends and meeting new people. They also have yoga available so that s awesome! I got the cacao and another turmeric chai and it was so calming. I think they add a bunch of herbs to it to give you that calming, relaxing effect. I definitely felt that. Would definitely go again, and get more chai here. Do check them out!!
Fantastic, beautiful space

Mainly, Im very happy  that something like this exists! I attended an intimacy event with Victoria and it supported growth in my marriage - and thats huge. On the negative side, the Jasmine tea was the most Ive paid at $13 for a pot of tea, took 10 minutes to arrive and was not as good as any of the tea I have at home from three organic brands. Parking was a challenge. The door person for the event first refused to take cash, then could not read the card automatically and had to enter it in, then said her machine could not process our credit card and finally asked us to buy the ticket (with the same card) on event-brite and asked us to step out of the way from holding up the line. If you dont want to hold up the line its simple: accept peoples money, starting with cash. Stepping back, I think most relationships fail because of this protocol, expressed in various forms along these lines: Person A) I am not equipped to connect with you in a way that would be easy and graceful for you. Nor do I plan to fix that. If you want to relate to me you have to solve my incompetencies or leave. Person B) Why should I have to solve your problems... Im leaving. I do think its mildly paradoxical that a center to facilitate relationships and community is the least capable of accepting energy in the form of money of any business Ive encountered in many months, particularly in a context where most community enterprises fail due to lack of money and money competence. When I went to pay for my tea something similar happened: My first card did not read when I tapped it (it works everywhere else). They said that happens often so I tried another card, which did work, making it hard to pay for tea and very hard to pay for an event. I think it is far more important that centers for community exist than how well they accept money. I also think that community is a phenomena that succeeds or fails based on competency. The easiest way to measure the competency of flow objectively is around money. All communities in our culture require some amount of money to be sustainable. So money is important after all for what it tells. I would not expect the social competency of a group to be higher than their competency for managing money, which is 100 times easier than managing psyches.

An absolute hidden gem. This is a very zen place to grab some amazing tea or a snack, join in on a yoga or Qigong/Thai Chi class, or just chill. Great space that is inviting, relaxing and centering (you see what I did there). Sometimes you get sim obnoxious zoomers who are on calls treating the space like their personal office and yelling, but most other guests are respectful. Will return here every time I am in town now that I have found it.

Mellow vibe. Staff is mostly volunteers and it can show in aloofness and responsiveness to basic things. There have been recent price increases on things and the admin staff is not very receptive to feedback about the events they host, even when those events were outright bad or a waste of people s time and money. Leaving 4 stars because for the most part it s a good experience for what it is and you can t ask for much. They do run the place with intention but definitely some things could be improved around service and offerings.
A mellow place to reconsider one s career trajectory in tech.

definitely my fav sanctuary in the city. the vibe is super chill with a tinge of mystical in the air -- perfect place to hang out with friends or read a book by yourself. i absolutely love the events at center. i have been trying to go to the sound baths whenever they become available. i feel thoroughly blessed each time.
A magical place!

Super calm area to grind or just hang. I noticed the deep community aspect when I went which is welcoming! There were also yoga classes going on when I went. Got a Shakti chai tea which was super good! Love the additions in there. Overall, an interesting and calm place to go
The students were friendly and had a strong sense of community, the amenities were clean and high quality, and the ambiance was soothing and beautiful.
Gem of a place in the midst of hustle bustle.
My favorite spot in SF. Amazing community gathering place. Unsurpassed ambience . Wish they had some food and coffee but otherwise couldnt ask for anything more.

nice space, wanted to like it.  interesting vibe, I tried to purchase a pass on site and the member/employee said it would be easier to do it by myself via phone.  I did that, while he began to make out with a regular.  I purchased a 3 class intro pass, without knowing or being told that it expired within a month. Only got to use 1/3 classes.

ReviewContent: Beautiful, relaxing community space   the cacao is delicious!

Yoga, tea, this is the cutest yoga studio I have ever visited. The studio is has a lot of comfortable sitting to hang around and tastefully decorated. Spend a day at the Center is one of my best day in San Fran
I love you the center SF, you re the best place on earth .

Ah, The Center! This place is such a gem in the city. Incredible vibes, welcoming people, delicious tea + cacao, and tons of creative / healing events. I love the comfy seating and beautiful studio space for yoga + dance. I really found community here.
Absolutely beautiful space and vibe. Have been here for events, yoga and tea with friends and love it. Wonderful community and can t wait to spend more time here!
Came here for an open mic in the tea room. This place has a spiritual vibe to it. Met some great people. The decor is very cozy and intimate.

We were here for a SOFAR SF concert in their backyard and my partner got bitten by a rat. The people at the centre went on to apologize and stated they had laid 8 rat traps and were befuddled how the rat managed to escape those rat traps and managed to go up my partner s shirt and bite him. They also did NOT inform the remaining guests of the rat which was still very much there running around and continued with the concert as though nothing happened. Being a cafe, this is gross negligence and a health violation so an inspection is warranted.

I was at a Sofar concert yesterday at The Center, and I was attacked by a WILD RAT. We were all sitting in the backyard. Out of nowhere, a rat just ran up inside my shirt, ran all over me, and bit me until I pulled it out. I was wriggling around for half a minute with a wild rat inside my shirt. I had to go to the emergency room right away. Multiple people saw this happen (including the venue organizer), and yet the concert was not stopped. No one else was informed that there was a wild rat running around. The person from the venue said they had 8 rat traps in place and couldnt understand how this had happened. Maybe hosting an event with over 50 people sitting on the floor wasnt the greatest idea if you have a known rat problem? No one bothered to call up later and check on me (despite having taken my friends number). The one silver lining was that the person at the venue offered me a first aid kit right away. I cannot believe something like this is taken so lightly. Having a wild rat running around which attacked someone is a huge health hazard to the audience. I cannot believe the event was organized in the first place, and even worse, continued despite the venue clearly knowing about the rat problem beforehand.
What an incredible space! Friday night open mic was beautiful and so welcoming. Cant wait to come back. Plus the chai tea latte was incredible. Warm and cozy all around!!
Great place

Oh my goodness how, I m so impressed with this place! The atmosphere there is so naturally chill, relaxed, calm and friendly. And it s a very-very beautiful place both inside and outside. *Also best mint tea in the city!
The absolute best public place in San Francisco - Thank God for the Center SF

A very calming tea cafe cum yoga studio. There s a lot of floor seating, a ton of pillows all over and huge Persian carpets to set the vibe right. A pot of tea is $12 and will serve 2-3 people pretty well (IMO). I tried a Vanilla Mint and another one I can t recall the name of - they were both refreshing, and satisfying. Much like the Vinyasa Yoga class I had the pleasure of taking. Love this place for a long and focused work session! Would recommend :D
One of my favorite spaces in the city. Calm atmosphere and kind staff. The drinking chocolate is my favorite thing to order. There are many great tea options to choose from and areas to sit and chat.
This is a relatively quiet and peaceful space. Great for long conversations, writing, reading or a relaxing escape from the hustle and bustle of the city.

I stumbled across this place and I feel so lucky. If you need a nice place to get away and relax from busy city life, this is the place for you. Its literally tucked away. You need to walk down a little alley and walk down the stairs to get to it. Once you walk in, take your shoes off and put them in the shelf to you right. Then walk up to the desk and order the tea you like. When I came here, I had a cold so I ordered the ginseng detox, recommended by one of the workers, and it cleared my sinuses right up. There are plenty of coxy little spots for you to cuddle up and read a book, or have an intimate chat with one another. The lighting is low and really makes the mood comfortable. I think its well worth it. If I lived here, I would definitely buy one. The workers that are here volunteer their time, they arent paid. The focus of this place is to create a community, make connections, heal, and transform yourself. I really wish we had a place like this where I lived. Everyone in here was so kind. Just full of good people, you know?
Friendly, great atmosphere.

Incredibly racist. Unfortunately, Ive spent over a year trying to work with the staff to do an event and they have ignored me and selected white meditation facilitators over and over again Once again, if youre interested in supporting racist appropriating spaces. This is for you The 2 stars are for being an alcohol free option in a city filled with alcohol Im just so tired of places that claim to be conscious but lack the action in actually being open minded and diverse.

ReviewContent: Very good place and activities
Beautiful relaxed tea house with lots of floor seating and pillows. Kind and open people gather here.
Really great and unique teahouse/yoga place
A beautiful space for yoga and tea, or just chatting with friends. Great place to do a social meet up.
Cozy place to read a book or visit with a friend
Peace and chai.
Great place to get tea
Great space for spiritual or yoga events. Great tea. Chill. They suggest no digital device use after 7PM. Ouch ...
Love this place. Gives a great energy and vibe. Great to unwind after a busy working day. The tea choice is good, very nice and helpful stuff.

First of all this is the most expensive tea on the planet. My girl friend wanted me to go with her to an all day event there that was supposed to have privet sessions. Well good luck getting on the list, everyone was standing on each other to get on the list (worst vibe ever).I finally got on one of the lists and they took me off, with out telling me. An hr later when I found out I get some 0 accountability excuse about a list mix up.
A peaceful place to connect with high vibrational energies.

Wow! I walked by randomly in a furious haste to get home in order to calm my frustration from a recent phone call. I was super curious so I took the detour down the long walkway into what is now one of my most favorite tea spots in this city. You walk in and immediate feel a sense of calm and relaxation. The tea lounge is beautiful and worldly with a great combination of people from all walks of life. The business person taking a break from their busy day, to the writer who looks centered and focused on every written word. The travelers who just met but seem to share a special connection, embarking on a possible friendship. Everyone from all walks of life should stop in and take a moment for themselves. Grab a cup of tea and be mindful. You wont regret it.

Its a good place for relaxing. You can clean your mind after a busy day. A big variety of yogas class. Nice staff. They are very friendly and they can help you if you have any questions. It will be a good experience if you wanna try something new. Recommended.
A place with heart and soul. A great place to relax and be around friendly and open people.

The server was nice and let me smell all the teas I asked. Its a chill atmosphere, warm, as our host put it, and this place offers wifi in additional to 5G (I believe) -- for free! I also find it easier to work in than some other places (at least in one of the rooms) with music playing and Im a person who likes to work in quiet spaces; though I do still wish the music was softer, if not nonexistent. They also have these AWESOME cushions on which you can sit and they are REALLY comfortable, offer great support, and are probably good for posture. Im actually going to look into getting one for myself. Lastly, they have a separate room that can host classes which I find unique, great for individual and community betterment, and cool. *Disclaimer: I was offered a free pot of tea in exchange for a review.

Peaceful atmosphere, bit of trouble to find. Just follow the signage from the street and look for the door down the alley to your left. As a tourist, I found myself wishing we had a place like this in town. Offers memberships for unlimited tea and community classes. Accommodating and friendly staff. Very low key. Tea by the cup or the pot.

Love this space and the community it represents and brings! I got lots of work done there amongst the persian rugs and morrocan style set up. A geniune and wonderful place with good energy and people! Thank you! And the tea is amazing!
Mikey, Your passion for providing a beautyfull space to treat your body and mind with love and goodness is refreshing to see in SF! Love it all ways Shawn
Great location, great tea, nice atmosphere. Staff was knowledgeable
Ayurveda yoga poses workshop
Super relaxing atmosphere. Comfy seating areas.  Sometimes theres even chill live music!
Wonderful, wonderful place. So relaxing, such a calm friendly environment. No pressure vibe.
